{"article_id":"3HNQTJ0CCqVSlHNi","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"ANNAPOLIS , Md .","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"( ) -","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"A man","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"who had a long-running feud with an Annapolis newspaper","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"blasted his way through its newsroom with a shotgun on Thursday ,","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"killing at least five people in one of the deadliest attacks","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"recorded on a U.S. media outlet ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"authorities said .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"The suspect fired through a glass door ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"looked for victims","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"and then sprayed the newsroom of the Capital Gazette newspaper group in Annapolis with gunfire ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"police and a witness said .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Acting police chief of the Anne Arundel County Police Department William Krampf told a news conference","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"that Capital Gazette assistant editor Rob Hiaasen , 59 , was among the victims .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Wendi Winters , 65 , Rebecca Smith , 34 , Gerald Fischman , 61 , and John McNamara were also killed ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"Smith was a sales assistant","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"and the others were journalists .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"\" This was a targeted attack on the Capital Gazette , \"","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Krampf said .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"\" This person was prepared to shoot people .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"His intent was to cause harm . \"","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"The suspect is Jarrod Ramos , 38 , of Laurel ,","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"the Capital Gazette and Baltimore Sun reported ,","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"citing law enforcement .","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"Anne Arundel County police said on Twitter","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"that due to investigative reasons , they have not released the name of the suspect in custody ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"adding","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"that as of Thursday evening , the suspect has not been booked .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"In 2012 , Ramos brought a defamation lawsuit against Eric Hartley , formerly a staff writer and columnist with publication The Capital , and Thomas Marquardt , then editor and publisher of The Capital ,","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"according to a court filing .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"In 2015 , Maryland ' s second-highest court upheld a ruling in favor of the Capital Gazette and a former reporter","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"who were accused by Ramos of defamation .","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"Related Coverage","depth":4},{"id":34,"text":"Factbox :","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"Victims of mass shooting at Maryland newsroom","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"According to a legal document ,","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"the article contended","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"that Ramos had harassed a woman on Facebook","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"and that he had pleaded guilty to criminal harassment .","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"The court agreed","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"that the contents of the article were accurate","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"and based on public records ,","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"the document showed .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"Ramos said on Twitter","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"that he had set up an account","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"to defend himself ,","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"and wrote in his bio","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"that he was suing people in Anne Arundel County","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"and \" making corpses of corrupt careers and corporate entities . \"","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"Phil Davis , a Capital Gazette crime reporter , said","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"he was hiding under his desk along with other newspaper employees","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"when the shooter stopped firing ,","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"the Capital Gazette reported on its website .","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"The newsroom looked \" like a war zone , \"","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"he told the Baltimore Sun ,","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"adding ,","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"\" I don ' t know","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"why he stopped . \"","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"\" As much as I ' m going to try to articulate how traumatizing it is to be hiding under your desk ,","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"you don ' t know","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"until you ' re there","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"and you feel helpless , \"","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"Davis said .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"Police officers in the Maryland capital of Annapolis responded within a minute to a 911 call about a shooting in progress","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"and apprehended the suspect","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"who was hiding under a desk ,","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"authorities said .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"Police are treating the shooting as a local incident , with no links to terrorism ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"a law enforcement source told .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Krampf did not say","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"why the gunman may have targeted the newspaper or its employees .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"When police found the suspect ,","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"his weapon was on the ground and \" not in his immediate proximity , \"","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"Steve Schuh , Anne Arundel county executive , told cable news station CNN .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"Law enforcement officials survey the scene","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"after a gunman fired through a glass door at the Capital Gazette newspaper","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"and sprayed the newsroom with gunfire ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"killing at least five people","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"and injuring several others , in Annapolis , Maryland , U.S. , June 28 , 2018 .","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"/Joshua Roberts","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"Police said","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"they recovered what they thought","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"might have been an explosive device","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"but Krampf later said","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"the suspect had smoke grenades .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"Investigators were in the process","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"of securing his Maryland residence","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"and obtaining search warrants ,","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"The suspect appeared to have damaged his fingertips","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"to try to avoid detection","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"and was refusing to cooperate with law enforcement ,","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"Baltimore TV station WJZ and other local media reported .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"Krampf did not comment on those reports .","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"Capital Gazette runs multiple newspapers out of its Annapolis office","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"and the group includes one of the oldest newspapers in the United States , The Gazette ,","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"which traces its origins back to 1727 .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"The company , part of the Tronc Inc TRNC.O media group , publishes newspapers in and around Annapolis , home of the U.S . Naval Academy .","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"The papers have thrived","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"by focusing on local news in the shadows of two much larger competitors , the Washington Post and Baltimore Sun .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"Law enforcement in Baltimore and New York City deployed extra officers to the offices of the New York Times and other major media outlets as a precaution ,","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"authorities said .","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"The shooting drew the attention of media groups ,","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"including Reporters Without Borders ,","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"which said","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"it was deeply disturbed by the events in Annapolis .","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"White House spokeswoman Lindsay Walters said","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"that U.S. President Donald Trump had been briefed on the shooting .","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"\" My thoughts and prayers are with the victims and their families .","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"Thank you to all of the First Responders","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"who are currently on the scene , \"","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"Trump said in a tweet .","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders said on Twitter ,","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"\" A violent attack on innocent journalists","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"doing their job","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"is an attack on every American . \"","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"Jimmy DeButts , an editor at the Capital Gazette , tweeted","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"that he was devastated , heartbroken and numb .","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"\" I ' m in no position","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"to speak ,","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"just know","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"@ capgaznews reporters & editors give all","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"they have every day .","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"There are no 40 hour weeks , no big paydays","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"- just a passion","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"for telling stories from our community , \"","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"he wrote .","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"One of the group ' s flagship papers , The Capital , plans to publish a Friday edition ,","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"several reporters with the group said .","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"\" I can tell you this :","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"We are putting out a damn paper tomorrow , \"","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"reporter Chase Cook wrote on Twitter a few hours after the shooting .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":265,"left":0,"right":264,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"